  "prompt": "Is there any software that counts wifi speed and usage?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several software tools available that can help you monitor Wi-Fi speed and usage. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **NetSpot**: This is a Wi-Fi analysis tool that allows you to visualize, optimize, and troubleshoot wireless networks. It provides details on Wi-Fi signal strength, network speed, and usage.\n\n2. **Wireshark**: This is a network protocol analyzer that can capture and interactively browse the traffic running on a computer network. It can provide detailed insights into network performance and usage.\n\n3. **GlassWire**: This network monitoring tool shows you real-time usage statistics and detailed information about the applications and services using your network.\n\n4. **Bandwidth Monitor**: Tools like PRTG Network Monitor or SolarWinds Network Performance Monitor can track bandwidth usage and provide insights into network performance.\n\n5. **Speedtest by Ookla**: While primarily used for measuring internet speed, it also provides detailed statistics on connection performance over time.\n\n6. **NetWorx**: This is a simple and easy-to-use tool that helps you measure your network speed, usage, and performance.\n\nThese tools can help you ensure that your Wi-Fi network is operating efficiently and can provide insights into any issues that might be affecting your network performance.",
